      "id": "mpi-is-18b813b1a334",
      "title": "Intelligent Construction & Building Systems",
      "speaker": "",
      "abstract": "(ICBS) Group explores how advances in robotics, artificial intelligence, and spatial interfaces are transforming the way we design, fabricate, and assemble the built environment. This lecture introduces two complementary strands of the group's work: distributed robotic systems for on-site construction, in which bespoke machines are co-designed alongside the structures they assemble; and human–machine collaboration, which combines humans and robots towards flexible, intelligent fabrication and construction. Drawing on the group's current and past research, the talk discusses future directions for rethinking the relationships among humans, design, machines, and materials in construction. Samuel Leder Xiliu Yang",
